messages.message: hey team, as pauline and i also start to implement, can we share any WIP PRs or branches so that we're aligned and don't duplicate work. i have a draft pr for organizing the gemini extractor logic into diff "tasks" for classification + extraction, split classification + extraction, and extraction here (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72869) for us to use in build, which can be used in app runs as well.

Hey @ayesha.ali /@pauline.comising,  should we create a branch for this so all of us can work on it and once end to end is working we can add tests and merge it to master?
Or would you prefer working directly off master? What do you both suggest?
I’m down for a feature branch
we eventually need to merge into master, right? what would be the benefits of a feature branch?

pros
• Allows us to get interdependent parts of the code out faster and available to other devs (no need to wait for unit tests or CI).
• We’re still figuring things out and haven’t finalized the full approach yet. Writing tests and having a clean PR up now would add overhead.
cons
• a large PR towards the end to review
Let’s just work on a feature branch. I’ll create one.
